# {{projectName}}

A Tenkit White Label Apps project for Expo SDK 57.

This app can produce multiple branded native apps from one Expo codebase. Each App Variant has its own Slug, app name, URL scheme, bundle identifier, Android package, theme accent, EAS Project ID, icon set, splash assets, and web favicon.

## Highlights

- Built with Expo Router, TypeScript, and Expo SDK 57.
- Uses App Variants to switch native app identity at config and build time.
- Includes per-App Variant assets under `assets/<app-variant-slug>/`.
- Ships with a local Tenkit CLI for build preparation: `build`, `reset`, and `doctor`.
- Includes `expo-dev-client` for native development builds and `expo-system-ui` for native UI style handling.
{{#if isUnistylesStyling}}
- Uses Unistyles for generated UI styling. Customize themes and tokens in `unistyles.ts`.
{{/if}}

## Get Started

1. Install dependencies.

   ```bash
   {{packageManagerInstallCommand}}
   ```

2. Review the generated App Variants.

   ```text
   src/constants/app-variants.ts
   ```

The app code lives in `src/app`. This project uses Expo Router file-based routing.

## Build Preparation

Use the local Tenkit CLI when you are preparing native projects for a real App Variant build or local native run:

```bash
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} build
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} reset
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} doctor
```

`{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} build` asks for an App Variant, App Variant Environment, and platform. It pulls EAS environment variables into `.env.local`, verifies that the pulled `APP_VARIANT_SLUG` matches the selected App Variant, and then runs `expo prebuild --clean` for that native identity.

Before using build preparation:

1. Set `EXPO_OWNER` in `src/constants/project-config.ts` to your Expo account or organization. It starts blank on purpose, so build preparation fails clearly instead of using Tenkit's Expo account.
2. Create or link an EAS Project for each App Variant.
3. Paste each EAS Project ID into `src/constants/app-variants.ts`.
4. Add `APP_VARIANT_SLUG` to each App Variant's EAS environment.

A new App Variant Slug can seed creation of a new EAS Project. This project generates `{{appVariants.[0].slug}}` and `{{appVariants.[1].slug}}` as its ordered App Variant Slugs.

When an App Variant is linked to an existing EAS Project, that linked EAS Project is authoritative for owner and Slug. Run `eas init` to reconcile the generated local values with EAS.

For non-interactive CI usage, pass the selected values explicitly:

```bash
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} build --slug {{appVariants.[0].slug}} --env production --platform ios
```

`{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} reset` prepares the default App Variant for the development environment on both native platforms.

## Run the Prepared App

After build preparation has created native projects for the selected App Variant, start Metro:

```bash
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} start
```

Then run the prepared native project:

```bash
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} ios
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} android
```

## Select an App Variant

The default App Variant is selected by `defaultAppVariantId` in:

```text
src/constants/app-variants.ts
```

Inspect the resolved public Expo config for the default App Variant:

```bash
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} expo:config
```

Inspect a specific App Variant:

```bash
APP_VARIANT_SLUG={{appVariants.[1].slug}} {{packageManagerRunCommand}} expo:config
```

For repeated local work with one App Variant, copy `.env.example` to `.env.local` and set `APP_VARIANT_SLUG` there. `.env.local` is ignored by git and may also be rewritten by `{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} build` after it pulls values from EAS.

## App Variant Assets

Each App Variant has its own asset folder:

```text
assets/<app-variant-slug>/
```

Required App Variant assets:

- `icons/icon.png`
- `icons/android-icon-foreground.png`
- `icons/android-icon-background.png`
- `icons/android-icon-monochrome.png`
- `icons/splash-icon-light.png`
- `icons/splash-icon-dark.png`
- `icons/favicon.png`
- `app.icon/icon.json`

Shared product assets that are not part of native app identity belong in `assets/_global/`.

## Useful Commands

```bash
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} build  # prepare native projects for an App Variant
{{packageManagerTenkitCommand}} reset  # reset native projects to the default App Variant
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} start         # start Metro
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} ios           # run the prepared iOS native project
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} android       # run the prepared Android native project
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} web           # run the web app
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} typecheck     # run TypeScript
{{packageManagerRunCommand}} expo:config   # print the resolved public Expo config
```

## Useful Files

- `app.config.ts` resolves the selected App Variant into Expo native config.
- `.env.example` documents the local App Variant selection variable.
- `eas.json` defines tenant-neutral EAS build profiles.
- `src/constants/app-variants.ts` owns App Variant definitions.
- `src/constants/project-config.ts` owns the Expo Owner.
- `src/hooks/use-app-variant-config.ts` reads the resolved App Variant bootstrap data at runtime.
- `assets/_global/README.md` explains shared asset placement.

